'''Aníbal Casis Godoy Lemus''' ({{IPA|es|aˈniβal ɣoˈðoj|lang}}; born 10 February 1990) is a Panamanian professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Midfielder#Defensive midfielder|defensive midfielder]] for [[Major League Soccer]] club [[San Diego FC]] and [[Captain (association football)|captains]] the [[Panama national football team|Panama national team]].

==Club career==
Godoy started his career at [[Chepo F.C.|Chepo]] and moved abroad in November 2011 to join [[Godoy Cruz Antonio Tomba|Godoy Cruz]] on loan to play alongside compatriot [[Armando Cooper]] after being voted Player of the Year in Panama.<ref name=PanamaFutbol>[http://panamafutbol.com/?p=6376 Aníbal Godoy: “Siempre fue un sueño para mi”] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180929194703/http://panamafutbol.com/?p=6376 |date=29 September 2018 }} – PanamaFutbol {{in lang|es}}</ref> After returning to Chepo he moved to Europe in August 2013 when he signed for Hungarian side [[Budapest Honvéd FC|Honvéd Budapest]].<ref>[http://www.concacaf.com/es/article/panamas-godoy-joins-honved-2 Panameño Godoy firma para el Honved] – CONCACAF {{in lang|es}}</ref> He made his debut for them on 1 September 2013 against [[Kaposvári Rákóczi FC|Kaposvár Rákóczi]].

===San Jose Earthquakes===
Godoy signed for [[Major League Soccer|MLS]] side [[San Jose Earthquakes]] on 6 August 2015.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.mlssoccer.com/post/2015/08/06/san-jose-earthquakes-sign-25-year-old-panamanian-international-anibal-godoy |publisher=MLS |title=San Jose Earthquakes sign 25-year-old Panamanian international Anibal Godoy from Hungarian club |access-date=12 January 2017 |date=5 August 2015}}</ref> On 30 November 2017, he signed a new, multi-year contract with the club.<ref>{{cite web|title=Quakes re-sign midfielder Anibal Godoy|url=https://www.sjearthquakes.com/anibal-godoy-resigned|publisher=San Jose Earthquakes|date=30 November 2017|access-date=30 November 2017|archive-date=3 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200203011917/https://www.sjearthquakes.com/anibal-godoy-resigned|url-status=dead}}</ref> He took on the role of [[Captain (association football)#Vice-captain|vice-captain]] during the 2018 season.

===Nashville SC===
On 7 August 2019, it was announced that at the conclusion of the 2019 season, Godoy would move to [[Nashville SC (MLS)|Nashville SC]] ahead of their inaugural [[Major League Soccer|MLS]] season in 2020. San Jose would receive $650,000 of General Allocation Money in return.<ref>{{cite web|title=NEWS: Earthquakes Trade Anibal Godoy to Nashville SC|url=https://www.sjearthquakes.com/post/2019/08/07/news-earthquakes-trade-anibal-godoy-nashville-sc|publisher=San Jose Earthquakes|date=7 August 2019|access-date=7 August 2019}}</ref> He was released by Nashville following their 2024 season.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nashvillesc.com/news/nashville-soccer-club-2025-roster-decisions|title=Nashville Soccer Club Announces 2025 Roster Decisions|first=Nashville|last=SC|website=Nashville SC}}</ref>

===San Diego FC===
Godoy signed with MLS expansion club [[San Diego FC]] on 19 December 2024. The team announced Godoy had joined on a one-year contract with club options for the following two seasons.<ref>{{cite web |title=San Diego FC Signs Free Agent Midfielder Aníbal Godoy |url=https://www.sandiegofc.com/news/san-diego-fc-signs-free-agent-midfielder-anibal-godoy |website=SanDiegoFC.com |publisher=San Diego FC |access-date=19 December 2024}}</ref>

==International career==
With the [[Panama national under-20 football team|Panama under-20]] team, Godoy participated in the [[2007 FIFA U-20 World Cup]] in Canada.

Godoy made his senior debut for [[Panama national football team|Panama]] in a March 2010 [[Exhibition game#Association football|friendly match]] against [[Venezuela national football team|Venezuela]]<ref name=PanamaFutbol/> and has, as of October 2021, earned a total of over 110 caps, scoring three goals.<ref>[https://www.rsssf.org/miscellaneous/panama-recintlp.html Panama - Record International Players] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150417132750/http://www.rsssf.com/miscellaneous/panama-recintlp.html |date=17 April 2015 }} – RSSSF</ref> He also played at the [[2011 CONCACAF Gold Cup|2011]]<ref>[http://www.rsssf.com/tables/11gc-full.html CONCACAF Championship, Gold Cup 2011 – Full Details]{{dead link|date=February 2023|bot=medic}}{{cbignore|bot=medic}} – RSSSF</ref> and [[2013 CONCACAF Gold Cup|2013 Gold Cup]]s.<ref>[http://www.rsssf.com/tables/13gc-full.html CONCACAF Championship, Gold Cup 2013 – Full Details]{{dead link|date=February 2023|bot=medic}}{{cbignore|bot=medic}} – RSSSF</ref>

Godoy represented Panama in all four of its [[2017 CONCACAF Gold Cup|2017 Gold Cup]] matches, comprising three group stage matches and one quarter-final. He tallied one assist and was named to the Best XI of the group stages,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.espnfc.us/concacaf-gold-cup/59/blog/post/3159409/canadian-teenage-sensation-alphonso-davies-leads-gold-cup-best-xi|title=Canadian teenage sensation Davies leads Gold Cup group stage Best XI|work=ESPN FC|author=Arch Bell|date=18 July 2017|access-date=22 July 2017}}</ref> but ultimately scored an own goal in Panama's quarter-final match against [[Costa Rica national football team|Costa Rica]] and club teammate [[Marco Ureña]], resulting in the end of the tournament for Panama and Costa Rica's advancement to the semi-finals.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.foxsports.com/soccer/story/godoy-s-own-goal-gives-costa-rica-1-0-win-over-panama-072017|title=Godoy's own goal gives Costa Rica 1–0 win over Panama|work=Fox Sports|date=20 July 2017|access-date=22 July 2017}}</ref>

During the lead-up to the [[2018 FIFA World Cup|2018 World Cup]], Godoy was called up to the squad for friendlies against [[Denmark national football team|Denmark]] and [[Switzerland national football team|Switzerland]] on 22 and 27 March, respectively, along with San Jose teammate [[Harold Cummings]].<ref>{{cite tweet |author=Panamanian Football Federation |user=fepafut |number=971224866207731714 |title=Repasa la lista de 24 convocados #PanamáMayor por Hernán Darío Gómez para partidos de preparación de cara a @fifaworldcup_es #Rusia2018|date=7 March 2018 |access-date=10 May 2020|language=es}}</ref> In May 2018, he was named in Panama's 23-man [[Panama national football team|squad]] for the 2018 World Cup in [[Russia]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.goal.com/en-gb/news/revealed-every-world-cup-2018-squad-23-man-preliminary-lists/oa0atsduflsv1nsf6oqk576rb|title=Revealed: Every World Cup 2018 squad – Final 23-man lists |website=Goal.com|date=4 June 2018|access-date=10 May 2020}}</ref> He captained his national team at the [[2023 CONCACAF Gold Cup]], helping them reach the [[2023 CONCACAF Gold Cup final|final]], where they were defeated 1–0 by [[Mexico national football team|Mexico]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.rfi.fr/en/sports/20230717-gimenez-the-hero-as-mexico-down-panama-1-0-to-lift-9th-gold-cup |title=Gimenez the hero as Mexico down Panama 1-0 to lift 9th Gold Cup |publisher=RFI |date=17 July 2023 }}</ref> On 26 May 2026, he was named in the 26-man squad for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.fepafut.com/blog/2026/05/26/los-26-mundialistas-de-panama/ |title=Los 26 Mundialistas de Panamá |trans-title=Panama's 26-Man World Cup Squad |publisher=[[Panamanian Football Federation]] |date=May 26, 2026 |access-date=May 26, 2026 |language=es |archive-date=May 26, 2026 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20260526170649/https://www.fepafut.com/blog/2026/05/26/los-26-mundialistas-de-panama/ |url-status=live}}</ref>

==Personal life==
As of 27 February 2018, Godoy holds a [[Permanent residence (United States)|U.S. green card]], qualifying him as a domestic player for [[Major League Soccer|MLS]] roster purposes.<ref>{{cite web|title=NEWS: Two Earthquakes Players Obtain Green Cards, No Longer Occupy International Spots|url=https://www.sjearthquakes.com/post/2018/02/27/news-two-earthquakes-players-obtain-green-cards-no-longer-occupy-international-spots|publisher=San Jose Earthquakes|date=27 February 2018|access-date=27 February 2018}}</ref>

Godoy became a naturalized American citizen on March 31, 2025.<ref>{{cite instagram|user=a_godoy20 |author=Aníbal Godoy|postid=DH4YWFxBAMG |title=I am officially an American citizen. Thank you, United States, for opening the doors of this beautiful country to me and my family, especially the San Jose Earthquakes, Nashville SC, and San Diego FC, who have played an important role in the development of my life and that of my family here in the United States. #Nuncadesistas #Firmeza #Creer |date=March 31, 2025}}</ref>

